  "prompt": "What are some Yu-Gi-Oh! Apps?",
  "response": "There are several Yu-Gi-Oh! apps available for fans of the franchise, offering a range of experiences from digital card games to reference tools. Here are some popular ones:\n\n---\n\n### **Yu-Gi-Oh! Digital Card Games**\n1. **Yu-Gi-Oh! Duel Links**  \n   - Play a simplified version of the Yu-Gi-Oh! card game with fast-paced duels.  \n   - Features iconic characters, events, and anime-inspired content.  \n   - Available on iOS, Android, and PC (via Steam).  \n\n2. **Yu-Gi-Oh! Master Duel**  \n   - A more comprehensive and competitive version of the game, closely following the official TCG/OCG rules.  \n   - Offers ranked play, events, and solo modes.  \n   - Available on iOS, Android, PC, PlayStation, Xbox, and Nintendo Switch.  \n\n---\n\n### **Deck Building and Reference Tools**\n3. **Yu-Gi-Oh! Neuron** (Yuze)  \n   - An official app for organizing your physical deck, checking card databases, and preparing for tournaments.  \n   - Includes features like a deck builder, banlist updates, and tournament locator.  \n   - Available on iOS and Android.  \n\n4. **Yu-Gi-Oh! Card Database**  \n   - Unofficial apps like **YGOPRO Deck Builder** or **Yu-Gi-Oh! Database** offer extensive card searches, deck-building tools, and card rulings.  \n   - Available on iOS and Android.  \n\n---\n\n### **Other Yu-Gi-Oh! Apps**\n5. **Yu-Gi-Oh! Dicefury**  \n   - A dice-rolling game based on Yu-Gi-Oh! monsters.  \n   - Casual and fun, but less focused on the card game.  \n   - Available on iOS and Android.  \n\n6. **Yu-Gi-Oh! Duel Generation** (Discontinued but still accessible in some regions)  \n   - A former digital card game app with a single-player campaign and PvP modes.  \n\n---\n\n### **Utility Apps for Players**\n- **YGO Omega** (PC-only but worth mentioning)  \n  - A fan-made simulator for playing Yu-Gi-Oh! online with friends.  \n  - Not an official app but widely used by the community.  \n\n---\n\nThese apps cater to different aspects of the Yu-Gi-Oh! experience, whether you're a competitive player, casual fan, or collector. Make sure to check compatibility and availability in your region!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
